00:27:36.690 --> 00:27:40.390
In trying to recreate Foster's
flight, which she had described

00:27:40.390 --> 00:27:43.100
in exquisite detail,
I too had landed

00:27:43.100 --> 00:27:46.510
in the proverbial dark
wilderness of error.

00:27:46.510 --> 00:27:50.250
You may have noticed it already,
but I didn't see it for months.

00:27:50.250 --> 00:27:53.410
Indeed, Foster had claimed
that she'd flown at high speed

00:27:53.410 --> 00:27:56.400
over the trees to the
Salem gathering.

00:27:56.400 --> 00:27:58.290
And indeed, she had
done so on May 15

00:27:58.290 --> 00:28:01.120
when there was a bright
moon in the sky.

00:28:01.120 --> 00:28:04.880
But nowhere had she said
that she'd flown at night.

00:28:04.880 --> 00:28:07.080
This is the kind of thing that
makes you sit bolt upright

00:28:07.080 --> 00:28:09.010
in bed at 3:00 in the morning.

00:28:09.010 --> 00:28:12.430
As I did many, many months
after I'd written those lines.

00:28:12.430 --> 00:28:16.980
I went back and I reread every
account of the Satanic celebration.

00:28:16.980 --> 00:28:20.390
Not one of the 50 people
included a word about the dark,

00:28:20.390 --> 00:28:22.410
or about navigating the dark.

00:28:22.410 --> 00:28:25.770
In fact, no one seemed to have
had any trouble seeing at all.

00:28:25.770 --> 00:28:28.960
Some of the celebrants talked
about the color of the wine.

00:28:28.960 --> 00:28:32.220
Several confessed that they had
signed the Devil's book in red.

00:28:32.220 --> 00:28:36.220
Details they would've had
trouble ascertaining by moonlight.

00:28:36.220 --> 00:28:38.030
In part I was a victim
of my research.

00:28:38.030 --> 00:28:42.680
I had wanted to tie Foster's flight
to that of another woman who rode

00:28:42.680 --> 00:28:45.890
through the darkness in
1704, if on horseback.

00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:50.790 position:56%
I had wanted to stress how much the
dark, the velvety, sound-amplifying,

00:28:50.790 --> 00:28:55.520
disorienting, terrifying blackness
was a player in the story.

00:28:55.520 --> 00:28:59.240
And after all, everybody
knows witches fly at night.

00:28:59.240 --> 00:29:02.280
Of course when I went back
to look, there it was.

00:29:02.280 --> 00:29:06.290
Foster's granddaughter very
plainly tells the justices

00:29:06.290 --> 00:29:08.750
that the meeting had
taken place at noon.

00:29:08.750 --> 00:29:13.230
And so ultimately in the
final draft, a plush carpet

00:29:13.230 --> 00:29:16.780
of meadows unfurls below Anne
Foster as she flies to Salem --

00:29:16.780 --> 00:29:18.880
or at least swears that she did --

00:29:18.880 --> 00:29:22.380
over red maples, and
over meandering streams.

00:29:22.380 --> 00:29:26.540
There's a bright moon in the
sky which is no longer dark.

00:29:26.540 --> 00:29:31.020
There were, of course, no
flights through the air in 1692,

00:29:31.020 --> 00:29:32.500
or goblins in the parlor,

00:29:32.500 --> 00:29:36.440
or supernatural conspiracies
in a meadow.

00:29:36.440 --> 00:29:39.250
How then did these
things seem to happen?

00:29:39.250 --> 00:29:41.400
When you pry the whole
chapter apart,

00:29:41.400 --> 00:29:46.380
you see that it makes uncanny
and wholly modern sense.

00:29:46.380 --> 00:29:49.080
I tell you about Anne Foster,
because I hope that you may take

00:29:49.080 --> 00:29:52.340
from the book what I
took from my misreading.

00:29:52.340 --> 00:29:55.580
A reminder of how swiftly
we jump to conclusions.

00:29:55.580 --> 00:30:00.040
How easily ignorance and
information can lead us astray.

00:30:00.040 --> 00:30:02.000
Fear warps our thinking.

00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:04.610
Preconceived notions trip us up.

00:30:04.610 --> 00:30:07.500
We like to lead but explanations.

00:30:07.500 --> 00:30:10.820
Above all, the Salem history
reminds us of the importance

00:30:10.820 --> 00:30:15.480
of keeping our heads, even when
that leaves a question unresolved.

00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:18.140
Even when it leaves us off balance.

00:30:18.140 --> 00:30:20.890
That's an uncomfortable state.

00:30:20.890 --> 00:30:25.440
But as a later Bostonian
noted, bewilderment is crucial.

00:30:25.440 --> 00:30:28.190
We would be lost, in
fact, without it.

00:30:28.190 --> 00:30:33.300
"It seems probable", wrote Henry
James 200 years after the trials,

00:30:33.300 --> 00:30:35.350
"If we were never bewildered,

00:30:35.350 --> 00:30:38.200
there would never be a
story to tell about us."

00:30:38.200 --> 00:30:40.000
Thank you.

