00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:11.690
best-spoken men in the colony.

00:32:11.690 --> 00:32:12.990
They're terrified.

00:32:12.990 --> 00:32:15.800
They often are men who are able

00:32:15.800 --> 00:32:18.480
to reason very logically
and very nimbly.

00:32:18.480 --> 00:32:21.320
So that, for example, a woman
who comes into the court

00:32:21.320 --> 00:32:23.070
and says, "I'm not a witch.

00:32:23.070 --> 00:32:24.370
I've never practiced witchcraft.

00:32:24.370 --> 00:32:25.910
I don't even know what a witch is."

00:32:25.910 --> 00:32:30.240
Is immediately asked, "How then can
you be certain you're not a witch,

00:32:30.240 --> 00:32:31.600
if you don't know what a witch is?"

00:32:31.600 --> 00:32:33.120
So you see, the manner

00:32:33.120 --> 00:32:37.400
of questioning was [laughs] rather
circular, and rather imprisoning.

00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:39.620
It's exacerbated by the fact

00:32:39.620 --> 00:32:43.210
that confession comes rather
naturally to a Puritan.

00:32:43.210 --> 00:32:47.740
And this sense of inadequacy, and
the fear that you might actually,

00:32:47.740 --> 00:32:50.020
on some level be complicity.

00:32:50.020 --> 00:32:52.360
It's very close to the surface.

00:32:52.360 --> 00:32:57.290
So that you hear in the -- in some
of the testimony, people saying,

00:32:57.290 --> 00:33:00.550
